## Current development status

The primary discipline document is a **foundational draft with substantive content incomplete**. It presently ends during Principle 9. The shorter overview resources and selected core instruments are working drafts derived from that source. Many other files in this repository are development briefs that define intended scope without representing approved, validated, or implementation-ready resources.

See [`document-governance/Document-Status.md`](document-governance/Document-Status.md) for the file-by-file status register.

## Evidence and review boundary

Citation and evidence integration remain pending. The documents distinguish HCOS™ synthesis and proposed practice from independently validated findings. The repository should not be used as a substitute for legal, clinical, occupational-health, emergency, labor, human-resources, safety, or other specialized professional processes.

Before publication, implementation, clinical use, legal reliance, or formal adoption, apply the HCOS™ Citation and Evidence Integration Prompt, complete human evidence review, document unresolved claims, and obtain identifiable human approval.

## Human–AI collaboration

AI supported organization, conceptual comparison, language development, and preliminary synthesis. Human authorship, evidence verification, interpretation, professional review, approval, implementation, and accountability remain essential. AI-supported resources are organized as **collaborative instruments**; they do not independently own judgment, authority, or accountability.

